        <p> It's clear to see Chooby has spent a lot of time doing digital painting. His sense of form and colour is lovely and you can feel motion in the drapery of the clothes and the water. The subsurface scattering on the belly of the horse and its face is exceptionally well done, and immidiately conveys that this is no ordinary horse but something magical to the viewer. The composition suffers mostly from a lack of clear direction and well-distributed values. The cut of the canvas strikrd me as off as well. Some more planning during the sketching phase would benefit Chooby greatly, as there are some easy to fix perspective issues happening in the frame as well as doing more thumbnails to play around with different elements in his composition. The base composition is interesting but there seems to be some confusion regarding element hierarchy. One thing that seems to flatten the image is the same treatment across the board (the only exception being the horse's head). Keeping your background rough is okay, but you should be polishing your focal points more.
