        <h2 class="blog-post-title">furart</h2>
        <strong>Panelist: Choob </strong>
        <blockquote>
        <p><em>Composition and Design:</em> 2 - The idea is nice but I think needs work particularly on the scale. A lower camera angle might help, so we're closer to Aladdin and he's larger, and we're looking up at this towering genie. As it is right now, he feels tiny but she doesn't feel particularly huge if that makes sense. I also think you could have used the cloud direction to help too, Maybe have them darker and more cramped together closer to the genie, think stormclouds gathering. They use smoke and clouds in the disney movie like this to make the genies feel more powerful. </p>
        <p><em>Application of other Artistic Fundamentals:</em> 2 - The colours especially are quite nice, and you have some thought towards things like lighting. Planning out values for the whole piece first would help I think, like if you want the genie to be brightly glowing or dark, is the smoke from the lamp bright like steam or dark like from a fire, etc, these are all things a better value plan would help to sell, as well as separating foreground from background. You did well to render the body so much with a limited time, and there's some attention to edges like the cast shadow from one leg onto the other, that's really nice. More edge control like that all over would be really nice, clouds and smoke especially are really sold by how you blend them. I know you ran out of time but any kind of background would be better than nothing I think, we need a clear foreground, middleground and background, and for them to each have their own value usually. Readability is super important, at the moment the genie is much too close to the sky colour and values for example.</p>
        <p><em>Creativity and Originality:</em> 2 - I like the genie design and the idea of them being so big and feeling like the most important character. Aladdin is very basic though, and you could have been much more creative with how you use the background and even clouds to frame things and lead the eye better. </p>
