        <p><em>Application of other Artistic Fundamentals:</em> 1 - While there is some attention to texture on the tree etc, like the whorls in the wood, it's pretty loose and doesnt help show us the forms much. The character looks good and I like the use of solid shadow on him to show forms a lot, it doesn't work as well for the rest of the piece though. Maybe you could have done some drawings of trees using just pure black to see if you could learn some of how the shapes and texture can be seen even in two tones. I can see some shading on the trunk but it doesnt help much, it might have been better to use for the texture or some cast shadows instead of to shade large sections.</p>
