        <blockquote>
        <p><em>Composition and Design:</em> 3 - An ambitious, if simple composition. The idea in question is extremely solid, but is hampered by a strict adherence to the rules of perspective when it would have been better to ignore them in service of a more stylised presentation, akin to Art Nouveau or Art Deco. If there is anything to be changed in this composition, i would elect to either; remove/de-ehphamsize the clouds, or change background to a darker, more saturated color as the pale blues and grey's blend in with the petals creating an unnecesary amount of visual noise in an otherwise strong composition. </p>
        <p><em>Application of other Artistic Fundamentals:</em> 2 - The story telling expressed in the composition alone is probably this pieces greatest strength. The 3 tiers of story telling here is something i wouldnt have thought of personally, and that must be commended. however, it is clear that there is work to be done in many areas. The proportions of the characters and anatomy in general are you biggest sumbling points here. The old womans legs are drastically different sizes, everyones heads are just a bit too large, and the Dryad in particular looks a bit more emancipated than i assume you intended. That being said the colour choices, while simple, definitely play to the strengths of the piece and contribute to the almost calm whimsy that it captures.  </p>
        <p><em>Creativity and Originality:</em> 3 - As mentioned before, the story telling and concept of the composition are extremely strong. But thats just the idea. The attempt was extremely admirable, but it is clear that this was far out of the scope of your current skillset. Regardless of your current skillset, the your intention behind various design decisions is clear, and the picture is better for it, but it does feel like your idea was held back by your lack of experience  with art.  </p>
        <p><em>Materials and Media:</em> 0 - Im giving you a 0 on this mostly because it is clear that you are fairly new to digital art. you are familiar with some aspects of your chosen program, but dont understand others. You also seem to be similarly unfamiliar with the dynamics of digital painting which led to an clearly rushed product in a few aspects such as the trees leaves and clothing highlights. You shouldnt be discouraged by this fact however, this is an issue that isn't easily solved and takes time to overcome. The technical aspects of drawing and painting are long standing issues that will continue to be part of your struggle as an artist for life. everyone goes through it. dont worry. its normal. </p>
