        <blockquote>
        <p><em>Composition and Design:</em> 5 - Feels very much a fairy tale, and like a key moment in a story. The use of foliage is really nice, the tree closest to us on the left especially helps with the overall depth of things. Some parts feel a little flat or unfinished, like between the back of the prince's cloak and the furthest right tree trunk, or the bridge, but overall this piece is lovely and manages to have so much detail in it without it being overwhelming or distracting from the central scene.</p>
        <p><em>Application of other Artistic Fundamentals:</em> 4 - Everything works very well together, though there are some things whch I'm not so sure on. The bridge in the background feels like a placeholder, and some of the lilypads have different perspectives, though maybe this is to show them bobbing around on waves? I think some of your value choices are too close to each other; the frogs on the lilypads blend into their backgrounds, especially the ones nearer the bridge. Some more rendering of the light on the characters would be nice too, something to show the metal of the prince's crown, or some shadow to the girl's hair to give her head some more shape, it feels a bit flat at the moment. Very good job balancing all the detail going on in this piece though, and all the colours and values hold togther really nicely. </p>
