        <blockquote>
        <p><em>Composition and Design:</em> 4 - The piece is extremely well balanced in most respects. The colors all pop but dont detract from the central focus, everything leads to the central figures extremely naturally, and everything just works. my only really complaint about the composition itself is that the rim lighting is very weak on your central characters. There was a missed opportunity to really make your core elements elements stand out even more with a stronger focus on the lighting. </p>
        <p><em>Application of other Artistic Fundamentals:</em> 3 - This is a bit hard to place because some elements are so strong that they would normally constitute a 4 or even a 5/5 score, but other elements are comparitevely lackluster, to point where im unsure why they were included. the Color choices in general are fantastic , theres no denying that, however the application of Rim lighting and and value transitions leaves something to be desired. your choice in flats are so strong that it compensates for the comparitive lack of complexity in other areas and i genuinely wonder why you dont just forgo blending colours in favour of really leaning into those flats with some strong cellshading sometimes. Another aspect that needs to be mentioned is the linework, or the lack of it. Most of the linework is well placed and serves it function well, but some of it, namely on the frog prince's snout and clothing, feels unnecesary. i dont know if it was because of the tight deadline or you genuinely just forgot, but there are errant lines all over the frog prince that stand out on close inspection. the reason i bring it up is mostly that these errant lines are almost exclusively limited to the frog prince, and arent anywhere to be seen on the rest of the piece. this is a nitpick at best, but it had to be mentioned. also the frog prince looks more like a gecko with that long snout.  </p>
        <p><em>Creativity and Originality:</em> 3 - Despite the idea itself not being too original its a fully realised piece of work, and being one of the few romantically oriented pieces is something to appreicate too. Though i must confess, i dont understand why you want to fuck the frog.  </p>
        <p><em>Materials and Media:</em> 2 - aside from some rough color blending in places there isnt much to talk about.  </p>
