        <p><em>Application of other Artistic Fundamentals:</em> 2 - The fur from the instanity wolf is well the most impressive part of this, its just a very economical use of brush work to get a good effect. I also like the wolfs pose, however a little bit of refinement could have gone a long way to making him properly imposing or impish, depending on where you wanted to go with it. as it stands right now, it feels like hes caught in a weird middle ground between the two, but its still good.. The pigs arefunctional, but very basic. They dont really expresses any real level of competence beyond the bare minimum of anatomical knowledge and some good painting skill, and the same goes for the enviroment too.  </p>
