        <blockquote>
        <p><em>Composition and Design:</em> 4 - Strong graphic design, I really like you using the lighting as a tool not just as the focal point. Its really selling the forms of the rest of the piece too. I'm not sure about it being pure black at the top as well as the bottom, I feel like you could have the smoke be a gentler transition at either the top or bottom, not have them both like that. </p>
        <p><em>Application of other Artistic Fundamentals:</em> 3 - Very good job on the lighting, the faces underlit by it are top notch. Costume and character design is nice too, I'm not a big fan of the dwarf though, the design or the sharp edges on him. Some difference in edges in general would help this piece, the smoke especially being a mix of hard and very soft would look nicer. Sharp for the underlit faces and then softer as their features recede into the smoke kind of thing. I feel like you could experiment with different colour too, the light and underlit smoky heads should be blue but the soldier himself and his uniform doesnt have to be so similar to these. I understand about the time limitation though and I'm sure it'd look different if you had had time to do more on the soldier. </p>
