        <h2 class="blog-post-title">Axalalal</h2>
        <strong>Panelist: Choob </strong>
        <blockquote>
        <p><em>Composition and Design:</em> 2 - There's nice use of the diagonal path, and it adds some depth, automatically adds a little narrative since she's going somewhere. I think you should consider foreground background etc more though, at the moment we just have those trees and they don't feel very well placed in space or compositionally. You should try to frame the character and lead the eye where you want it to go, maybe do more thumbnails for the next one to experiment with different options.</p>
        <p><em>Application of other Artistic Fundamentals:</em> 1 - I like some of the attention to detail like the texture of the trees, or her hair and different layers of clothing, but there's a few things that need work. Her anatomy, particularly arms and hands are awkward and not proportional, she doesnt seem entirely placed on the path right, and I cant decide if those are small trees or she's a big girl. The colours overall aren't bad but you should think about values more and how you can use them to both draw attention where you want it to be as well as show what things are in the foreground vs background. I also think some of your detailing would have been better spent on the character than on the path. </p>
        <p><em>Creativity and Originality:</em> 1 - The character herself is nice but the rest of the piece is pretty sparse. I'm glad you have at least some background, but just having empty space behind the trees and grass is odd, and I think you could put in some more things next time to make the environment more interesting, wthout distracting from the character too much.</p>
        <p><em>Materials and Media:</em> 0 - You're not very comfortable with digital yet and I think you're thinking more in terms of drawing everything in different colours rather than painting them if that makes sense. Don't be afraid to use bigger brushes, especially for the environment stuff, and try out implying things. Drawing every outline isnt always necessary, you can show so much with some shadow shapes to describe forms. </p>
        </blockquote>

