        <p><em>Composition and Design:</em> 1 - I dont really understand whats going on in this. The girl is drawn in one perspective, and the ground is being drawn in a completely other, isometric persepctive. Its really strange because  </p>
        <p><em>Application of other Artistic Fundamentals:</em> 1 - The anatomy is very inconsistent, with different parts being disproportionately long or short, mostly at radnom. the perspective is odd and confusing, and the hatching is 'misplaced' to put it charitably. Hatching is its own topic and i could go into great deatil about it, but the short version is that your hatching needs to vary a lot more. hatching can be used to indicate shadows and texture. if the hatching is all the same, theres no point in having it at all. In this particular instance, it looks like you were so distracted by the hatching that you forgot to do much of anything else. It was certainly ambitious of you to do so much hatching, and i cant fault you for that.  </p>
        <p><em>Creativity and Originality:</em> 2 -  Despite how much i ragged on about the hatching, it wasnt a bad idea. Its just that you focused so much on hatching  and spent so long on it, when really you should have used that time to cleaning up the rest of your drawing.</p>
